{"id":"493b2351-3854-45aa-bc79-8c45ff2e87fb","title":"1507/04/20","type":"main-list-block","children":[{"id":"2d97c95e-59ce-4515-8a3c-9c7f5b6f2150","type":"standoff-editor-block","text":"From Bologna, April 20th, (1507).","standoffProperties":[{"id":"4555f021-f635-43a2-9dad-b0234617f416","type":"codex/entity-reference","start":0,"end":3,"value":"5d6c10e9-9430-49dd-b0fd-91f50e70558b","zeroPoint":false,"metadata":[]},{"id":"20de065b-831b-4f76-bbd3-c1cb15b8d1d2","type":"codex/entity-reference","start":5,"end":11,"value":"c8102ebc-3fb5-4919-975a-c0db203bcf85","zeroPoint":false,"metadata":[]},{"id":"524d28b6-6204-49d3-89bd-322b9d78c027","type":"codex/time-reference","start":14,"end":31,"value":"e66d9a6c-beb1-45a7-98a6-25371d2b5c8d","zeroPoint":false,"metadata":[]},{"id":"839bd46d-2f97-4a8c-904e-845db69209f1","type":"style/superscript","start":22,"end":24,"value":null,"zeroPoint":false,"metadata":[]}],"blockProperties":[]},{"id":"1f9588d6-ece9-4c20-a1c4-6ea22b604edc","type":"standoff-editor-block","text":"To Giovan Simone di Lodovico di Buonarrota Simoni,","standoffProperties":[{"id":"d744b745-b5fd-4e21-8811-b7aad2d5adc2","type":"style/italics","start":0,"end":49,"value":null,"zeroPoint":false,"metadata":[]},{"id":"767461fa-e26c-4d74-96f7-913e730f6ad7","type":"codex/entity-reference","start":3,"end":48,"value":"d8b71a68-0171-4aa5-a446-69fbdbd88655","zeroPoint":false,"metadata":[]}],"blockProperties":[{"id":"d744b745-b5fd-4e21-8811-b7aad2d5adc2","type":"style/italics","value":null,"metadata":[]}]},{"id":"7bb479c8-4379-4adc-8f5e-ce5df33e9edf","type":"standoff-editor-block","text":"in Florence.","standoffProperties":[{"id":"bc3e69a3-9a1f-4a52-af13-5823a35ab92a","type":"codex/entity-reference","start":0,"end":1,"value":"0c663cc2-dd9f-40ce-b17b-734e41b369ef","zeroPoint":false,"metadata":[]},{"id":"c7889300-6afe-47fe-800b-454f609a9778","type":"codex/entity-reference","start":3,"end":10,"value":"671ee7e7-ae1b-4a5a-9591-b40203d5108f","zeroPoint":false,"metadata":[]}],"blockProperties":[]},{"id":"0ac980ac-532f-4ad2-ae7e-54edd298159d","type":"standoff-editor-block","text":"","standoffProperties":[],"blockProperties":[]},{"id":"1d6d76e3-466d-4feb-971c-6b11d7c99258","type":"standoff-editor-block","text":"Giovan Simone, \u2014 I have not replied to a letter received from thee several days ago because I have not had the time. In this letter I have to tell thee that up to the present my work goes well, and accordingly I have hopes that it will finish satisfactorily \u2014 please God it may be so! And if it should be so \u2014 that is to say, if I come out of this affair well \u2014 I will come, or rather, return, to you immediately, and I will do all that I have promised each one of you; that is to say, I will help you with all I have \u2014 in what way you and our father will be able to judge for yourselves. Therefore be of good cheer, and be diligent in thy shop, making the most of every opportunity; for I hope that before long ye will be keeping a shop by yourselves and for yourselves. If ye understand the business and know how to trade it will be of very great assistance. Wherefore attend to thy work with diligence. Thou writest of a certain friend of thine, a doctor, who has told thee that the plague is a dangerous disease and that people die of it. I am very glad to know of this because it is very prevalent here and these Bolognesi have not yet learnt that it is fatal. Wherefore it would be a good thing if he were to come here, because then he would perhaps teach them by experience, and they would greatly benefit thereby. I have nothing more to tell thee. I am well and getting on satisfactorily: I hope soon to be back in Florence.","standoffProperties":[{"id":"2cf497cc-4be0-419c-9646-bea8925255a3","type":"style/uppercase","start":0,"end":13,"value":null,"zeroPoint":false,"metadata":[]},{"id":"ae462a4e-55d8-456a-bb11-66f6cb72153c","type":"codex/entity-reference","start":0,"end":12,"value":"d8b71a68-0171-4aa5-a446-69fbdbd88655","zeroPoint":fal